

AQARIONZ MEGATRON SOURCE MAP v2.0

Purpose:
Unified, self-adapting lattice connecting human, environmental, and digital signals with multi-agent AI, sovereignty principles, modular nodes, and phenomenological/metaphorical data. Designed for integration, extension, and live operation.


---

1. Core Architecture

1.1 Backbone Layers

Layer	Role	Data / Function

Signal Layer	Atomic unit of interaction	text, bio-signals, MIDI, IMU, environmental sensors, story/meta signals
Baseline Layer	Quiet/reference state	Cave darkness, river silence, heart rest, zero-input MIDI
Mapper Layer	Transform signals	Harmonics, sovereignty scores, story markers, paradox flags
Pattern Layer	Aggregate/reusable behaviors	Increasing resonance, inner ice, boundary compression, river drift, storm edge
Node Layer	Physical/digital deployment	Home, Cave, River, Storm, MIDI AQAROON
Multi-Agent Layer	AI orchestration	Sovereign agents, self-diagnosing, adaptive, plugin-ready



---

2. Signal Schema

{
  "signal_id": "UUID",
  "timestamp": "ISO8601",
  "channel": "text|midi|imu|env|bio",
  "payload": "raw data or symbolic",
  "context": {
    "location": "lat/lon or node-id",
    "environment": "temperature, humidity, CO2, EM",
    "user_state": "calm|agitated|meditative|unknown"
  },
  "mapper_results": {
    "harmonic_score": 0-1,
    "sovereignty_score": 0-1,
    "pattern_detected": "string",
    "paradox_flag": true|false
  }
}


---

3. Nodes & Deployment

Node	Hardware	Software	Role

Home	Laptop/RPi	AQARIONZ Core	Daily life signals, meditation, baseline testing
Cave	Sensors: IMU, CO₂, barometer	Core + Cave Module	Darkness baseline, boundary experiments
River	Sensors: flow, temp, sound	Core + River Module	Environmental patterns and story sync
Storm Porch	Sensors: wind, pressure, EM	Core + Storm Module	Extreme state logging, paradox triggers
MIDI	MIDI controller	Core + Mapper	Physical interface to harmonics, story arcs, sovereignty adjustments


Node Communication:

Multi-agent synchronization via encrypted, self-sovereign channels.

Publish/subscribe model: nodes push raw signals; multi-agent AI maps them.

Local logs ensure autonomy and privacy.



---

4. Multi-Agent AI Layer

Roles:

Signal Interpreter Agent: transforms raw input → patterns, harmonics, story markers

Sovereignty Agent: monitors choice, consent, and paradox flags

Self-Diagnosis Agent: checks mapper fidelity, detects drift, auto-corrects

Plugin Agent: negotiates new data sources or nodes safely

Paradox Reflection Agent: monitors Pinocchio paradox states in AI-human interactions


Communication Protocol:

gRPC/WebSocket between agents

Heartbeat + health checks

Immediate propagation of paradox flags to Sovereignty Agent



